{"pageid":67397,"pagename":"Hit delay","title":"Hit delay","displaytitle":"Hit delay","revid":14241033,"properties":[{"name":"smw-semanticdata-status","value":""},{"name":"description","value":"Hit delay is measured in game ticks and is the amount of time an attack will be queued to an entity (player or NPC) without doing damage. Specifically, hit delay measures the amount of ticks an attack is processed on an entity without damaging it. Melee attacks damage an entity the very first tick that they are processed, and as such, are defined to have a hit delay of 0."}],"content":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Hit delay</b> is measured in <a href=\"/w/RuneScape_clock\" title=\"RuneScape clock\">game ticks</a> and is the amount of time an attack will be queued to an entity (<a href=\"/w/Player_character\" title=\"Player character\">player</a> or <a href=\"/w/NPCs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NPCs\">NPC</a>) without doing damage. Specifically, hit delay measures the amount of ticks an attack is processed on an entity without damaging it. Melee attacks damage an entity the very first tick that they are processed, and as such, are defined to have a hit delay of 0.\n</p><p>The hit delay of distance attacks is typically variable based on the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chebyshev_distance\" class=\"extiw\" title=\"wikipedia:Chebyshev distance\"><span title=\"&quot;Chebyshev distance&quot; on English Wikipedia\">Chebyshev distance</span></a> between the entity dealing the attack and the entity receiving the attack. The distance is typically measured edge-to-edge in <a href=\"/w/Game_square\" title=\"Game square\">game squares</a>, using the same edge for both entities. I.e. distance will be calculated using an NPC's closest edge to the player, and the player's furthest edge from the NPC. However, <a href=\"/w/Barrage_spells\" title=\"Barrage spells\">barrage spells</a> are a notable exception in that they calculate distance from the player to an <a href=\"/w/Non-player_character\" title=\"Non-player character\">NPC's</a> south-west tile, which causes abnormally long hit delay when attacking a large NPC from the north or east. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\" role=\"navigation\" aria-labelledby=\"mw-toc-heading\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en-GB\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2 id=\"mw-toc-heading\">Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Processing_order_delay\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Processing order delay</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Melee\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Melee</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Ranged\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ranged</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#Bows_and_crossbows\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Bows and crossbows</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#Dark_bow\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dark bow</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#Chinchompas_and_thrown_category_weapons\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Chinchompas and thrown category weapons</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#Ballistae\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Ballistae</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#Dwarf_multicannon\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Dwarf multicannon</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#Magic\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Magic</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#Shield_specials\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Shield specials</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Processing_order_delay\">Processing order delay</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=1&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Processing order delay\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Processing order delay\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Attacks will hit on different ticks depending on whether the attacking or defending entity is processed first in a tick. If the entity receiving the hit is processed earlier than the entity dealing the hit, then the hit will be delayed by an additional one tick.\n</p><p><a href=\"/w/NPCs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NPCs\">NPCs</a> are processed earlier than players each tick, so this effect will make all hits on <a href=\"/w/NPCs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NPCs\">NPCs</a> delayed by an additional one tick compared to the numbers listed in this article.\n</p><p>In the case of <a href=\"/w/PvP\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PvP\">PvP</a>, <a href=\"/w/PID\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"PID\">PID</a> will be the determining factor whether or not processing order delay will delay attacks by one tick.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Melee\">Melee</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=2&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Melee\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Melee\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>When attacking using a melee weapon, with few exceptions such as the <a href=\"/w/Dragon_claws#Special_attack\" title=\"Dragon claws\">dragon claws special attack</a>, the hit delay is 0 game ticks.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ranged\">Ranged</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=3&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Ranged\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Ranged\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Bows_and_crossbows\">Bows and crossbows</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=4&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Bows and crossbows\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: Bows and crossbows\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Bow and crossbow projectiles, with the exception of the <a href=\"/w/Dark_bow\" title=\"Dark bow\">dark bow</a>'s second projectile, follow this table:\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />(squares)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>This delay follows this formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">B</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">o</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">w</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">l</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/43385f3f8e0df95b8bb23f07ab113cb58bf6b2c4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:33.582ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dark_bow\">Dark bow</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=5&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Dark bow\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: Dark bow\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/w/Dark_bow\" title=\"Dark bow\">dark bow</a> has a unique hit delay defined for its second projectile, and its two projectiles follow this table:\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(1st projectile)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay\n<p>(2nd projectile)\n</p>\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>5\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>The first projectile follows the standard bow projectile delay formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">B</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">o</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">w</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">l</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>3</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/43385f3f8e0df95b8bb23f07ab113cb58bf6b2c4\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:33.582ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {BowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {3+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>The second projectile follows a formula very similar to the magic formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {DarkBowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {2+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">k</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">B</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">o</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">w</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">l</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>2</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {DarkBowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {2+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/7be980e5f92bf4b62ec966ebac9e5c0566f28ec8\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:38.576ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {DarkBowDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {2+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Chinchompas_and_thrown_category_weapons\">Chinchompas and thrown category weapons</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=6&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Chinchompas and thrown category weapons\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: Chinchompas and thrown category weapons\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/w/Weapons/Types#Chinchompas\" title=\"Weapons/Types\">Chinchompas</a> and <a href=\"/w/Weapons/Types#Thrown_weapons\" title=\"Weapons/Types\">thrown weapons</a> (<a href=\"/w/Knives\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Knives\">knives</a>, <a href=\"/w/Dart\" title=\"Dart\">darts</a>, <a href=\"/w/Thrownaxes\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Thrownaxes\">thrownaxes</a>, and the <a href=\"/w/Toxic_blowpipe\" title=\"Toxic blowpipe\">toxic blowpipe</a>) have the following hit delay:\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />(squares)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>1<sup id=\"cite_ref-blowp_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-blowp-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>1<sup id=\"cite_ref-blowp_1-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-blowp-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"references-small hideQuotes\"><div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-blowp-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-blowp_1-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-blowp_1-1\">1.1</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">The <a href=\"/w/Toxic_blowpipe#Special_attack\" title=\"Toxic blowpipe\">toxic blowpipe special attack</a> has a hit delay of 2 ticks when distance is 4 or 5.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p>This delay follows the formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {ThrownDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {\\mathit {Distance}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">T</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">h</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">r</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">o</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">w</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">l</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {ThrownDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {\\mathit {Distance}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/b065d78946530b318e5f45f4cba2df85fba281cc\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:33.083ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {ThrownDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {\\mathit {Distance}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd>\n<dd></dd></dl>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Ballistae\">Ballistae</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=7&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Ballistae\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: Ballistae\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p><a href=\"/w/Ballista\" title=\"Ballista\">Ballistae</a> have the following hit delay:\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />(squares)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Dwarf_multicannon\">Dwarf multicannon</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=8&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Dwarf multicannon\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: Dwarf multicannon\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>The <a href=\"/w/Dwarf_multicannon\" title=\"Dwarf multicannon\">dwarf multicannon</a>, despite being able to attack targets at distances as far away as 19 tiles, does not have any hit delay.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Magic\">Magic</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=9&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Magic\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: Magic\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Most magic projectiles, including <a href=\"/w/Spells\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Spells\">spells</a> and projectiles from <a href=\"/w/Weapons/Types#Powered_staves\" title=\"Weapons/Types\">self-powered staves</a>, follow this table.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />(squares)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>1\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>11<sup id=\"cite_ref-barrage_2-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-barrage-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>5\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>12<sup id=\"cite_ref-barrage_2-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-barrage-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>5\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>13<sup id=\"cite_ref-barrage_2-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-barrage-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>5\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>14<sup id=\"cite_ref-barrage_2-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-barrage-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>6\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>15<sup id=\"cite_ref-barrage_2-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-barrage-2\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</td>\n<td>6\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<div class=\"references-small hideQuotes\"><div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-barrage-2\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\">↑ <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-barrage_2-0\">1.0</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-barrage_2-1\">1.1</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-barrage_2-2\">1.2</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-barrage_2-3\">1.3</a></sup> <sup><a href=\"#cite_ref-barrage_2-4\">1.4</a></sup></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a href=\"/w/Barrage_spells\" title=\"Barrage spells\">Barrage spells</a> calculate hit delay using the distance from an NPC's south-west tile, therefore hit delay can be observed for distances greater than 10 tiles on large <a href=\"/w/NPCs\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"NPCs\">NPCs</a> such as <a href=\"/w/Scorpia\" title=\"Scorpia\">Scorpia</a>.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p>This gives this likely formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {MagicDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {1+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">M</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">g</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">l</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n            <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">y</mi>\n          </mrow>\n        </mrow>\n        <mo>=</mo>\n        <mn>1</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>1</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>3</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {MagicDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {1+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/1f971807d549803175d6d56846fd7a197e945500\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:35.34ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle {\\mathit {MagicDelay}}=1+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {1+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{3}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<p>However, <a href=\"/w/Grasp_spells\" title=\"Grasp spells\">grasp</a> and <a href=\"/w/Demonbane_spells\" title=\"Demonbane spells\">demonbane spells</a> from the <a href=\"/w/Arceuus_spellbook\" title=\"Arceuus spellbook\">Arceuus spellbook</a> have a hit delay of 2 ticks no matter the distance between the caster and target.\n</p>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Shield_specials\">Shield specials</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?section=10&amp;veaction=edit\" class=\"mw-editsection-visualeditor\" title=\"Edit section: Shield specials\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-divider\"> | </span><a href=\"/w/Hit_delay?action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: Shield specials\">edit source</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<p>Shield special attacks such as the <a href=\"/w/Dragonfire_shield\" title=\"Dragonfire shield\">dragonfire shield</a>, <a href=\"/w/Dragonfire_ward\" title=\"Dragonfire ward\">dragonfire ward</a>, and <a href=\"/w/Ancient_wyvern_shield\" title=\"Ancient wyvern shield\">ancient wyvern shield</a> follow this table.\n</p>\n<table class=\"wikitable\">\n<tbody><tr>\n<th>Distance<br />(squares)\n</th>\n<th>Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n</th></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>1\n</td>\n<td>2\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>2\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>3\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>4\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>5\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>6\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>7\n</td>\n<td>3\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>8\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>9\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td>10\n</td>\n<td>4\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p>This gives the likely formula:\n</p>\n<dl><dd><span class=\"mwe-math-element\"><span class=\"mwe-math-mathml-inline mwe-math-mathml-a11y\" style=\"display: none;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"  alttext=\"{\\displaystyle 2+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {4+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\">\n  <semantics>\n    <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n      <mstyle displaystyle=\"true\" scriptlevel=\"0\">\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mo>+</mo>\n        <mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230A;</mo>\n          <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n            <mfrac>\n              <mrow>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n                <mo>+</mo>\n                <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                  <mrow class=\"MJX-TeXAtom-ORD\">\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">D</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">i</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">s</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">t</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">a</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">n</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">c</mi>\n                    <mi class=\"MJX-tex-mathit\" mathvariant=\"italic\">e</mi>\n                  </mrow>\n                </mrow>\n              </mrow>\n              <mn>6</mn>\n            </mfrac>\n          </mrow>\n          <mo>&#x230B;</mo>\n        </mrow>\n      </mstyle>\n    </mrow>\n    <annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">{\\displaystyle 2+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {4+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }</annotation>\n  </semantics>\n</math></span><img src=\"https://wikimedia.org/api/rest_v1/media/math/render/svg/01b9e5081c21845aa662ee9992c7b7c4851a9545\" class=\"mwe-math-fallback-image-inline\" aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"vertical-align: -2.505ex; width:20.378ex; height:6.176ex;\" alt=\"{\\displaystyle 2+\\left\\lfloor {\\frac {4+{\\mathit {Distance}}}{6}}\\right\\rfloor }\"/></span></dd></dl>\n<table class=\"navbox nowraplinks mw-collapsible\" data-expandtext=\"show\" data-navbox-name=\"Combat Mechanics\" data-collapsetext=\"hide\"><tbody><tr><th colspan=\"2\" class=\"navbox-title\" id=\"navbox-title\"><div class=\"navbox-title-name-notplain\"><div class=\"navbar\" style=\"float:left;text-align:left;width:6em\"><div class=\"plainlinks noprint\" style=\"background-color:transparent;padding:0;font-weight:normal;font-size:xx-small;white-space:nowrap\"><a href=\"/w/Template:Combat_Mechanics\" title=\"Template:Combat Mechanics\"><span title=\"View this template\">v</span></a>&#160;<span style=\"font-size:80%\">&#8226;</span>&#160;<a class=\"text\" href=\"https://oldschool.runescape.wiki/w/Template_talk:Combat_Mechanics\"><span title=\"Discussion about this template\">d</span></a>&#160;<span style=\"font-size:80%\">&#8226;</span>&#160;<a class=\"text\" href=\"https://oldschool.runescape.wiki/w/Template:Combat_Mechanics?action=edit\"><span title=\"Edit this template\">e</span></a></div></div><span>Combat Mechanics</span></div></th></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\"><a href=\"/w/Combat\" title=\"Combat\">Combat</a></td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Attack_range\" title=\"Attack range\">Attack range</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Attack_speed\" title=\"Attack speed\">Attack speed</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Auto_Retaliate\" title=\"Auto Retaliate\">Auto Retaliate</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Autocast\" title=\"Autocast\">Autocast</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Combat_triangle\" title=\"Combat triangle\">Combat triangle</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Special_attacks\" title=\"Special attacks\">Special attacks</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Hitsplat\" title=\"Hitsplat\">Hitsplat</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Tanking\" title=\"Tanking\">Tanking</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Magical_melee\" title=\"Magical melee\">Magical melee</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Magical_ranged\" title=\"Magical ranged\">Magical ranged</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Ranged_magic\" title=\"Ranged magic\">Ranged magic</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\">Maximum hit</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Maximum_magic_hit\" title=\"Maximum magic hit\">Maximum magic hit</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Maximum_melee_hit\" title=\"Maximum melee hit\">Maximum melee hit</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Maximum_ranged_hit\" title=\"Maximum ranged hit\">Maximum ranged hit</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Monster_maximum_hit\" title=\"Monster maximum hit\">Monster maximum hit</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\">Damage per second</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Damage_per_second/Melee\" title=\"Damage per second/Melee\">Damage per second/Melee</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Damage_per_second/Ranged\" title=\"Damage per second/Ranged\">Damage per second/Ranged</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Damage_per_second/Magic\" title=\"Damage per second/Magic\">Damage per second/Magic</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\">Mechanics</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Aggressiveness\" title=\"Aggressiveness\">Aggressiveness</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Flinching\" title=\"Flinching\">Flinching</a></li>\n<li><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Hit delay</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Retaliation\" title=\"Retaliation\">Retaliation</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Retreat\" title=\"Retreat\">Retreat</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Safespot\" title=\"Safespot\">Safespot</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Spawning\" title=\"Spawning\">Spawning</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Successful_hit\" title=\"Successful hit\">Successful hit</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Tolerance\" title=\"Tolerance\">Tolerance</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Wander_radius\" title=\"Wander radius\">Wander radius</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/PJ_timer\" title=\"PJ timer\">PJ timer</a></li></ul></td></tr><tr class=\"navbox-group\"><td class=\"navbox-group-title\">Other</td><td class=\"navbox-list\">\n<ul><li><a href=\"/w/Single-way_combat\" title=\"Single-way combat\">Single-way combat</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Multicombat_area\" title=\"Multicombat area\">Multicombat area</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Singles-plus_combat\" title=\"Singles-plus combat\">Singles-plus combat</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/w/Player_killing\" title=\"Player killing\">Player killing</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nParsed by mediawiki‐67df7655d‐7qtxl\nCached time: 20220421154803\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\n[SMW] In‐text annotation parser time: 0 seconds\nCPU time usage: 0.152 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.368 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 235/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 6896/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 54/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 5/100\nExpensive parser function count: 0/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 1914/5000000 bytes\nLua time usage: 0.015/10.000 seconds\nLua memory usage: 906175/367001600 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   50.946      1 -total\n 45.00%   22.928      2 Template:Reflist\n 33.88%   17.259      1 Template:Combat_Mechanics\n 18.18%    9.262      1 Template:Navbox\n  8.17%    4.164      1 Template:Ctg\n  3.73%    1.903      1 Template:Wp\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:67397-0!canonical!math=5 and timestamp 20220421154802 and revision id 14241033. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"'''Hit delay''' is measured in [[RuneScape clock|game ticks]] and is the amount of time an attack will be queued to an entity ([[Player character|player]] or [[NPCs|NPC]]) without doing damage. Specifically, hit delay measures the amount of ticks an attack is processed on an entity without damaging it. Melee attacks damage an entity the very first tick that they are processed, and as such, are defined to have a hit delay of 0.\n\nThe hit delay of distance attacks is typically variable based on the {{wp|Chebyshev distance}} between the entity dealing the attack and the entity receiving the attack. The distance is typically measured edge-to-edge in [[game square]]s, using the same edge for both entities. I.e. distance will be calculated using an NPC's closest edge to the player, and the player's furthest edge from the NPC. However, [[barrage spells]] are a notable exception in that they calculate distance from the player to an [[Non-player character|NPC's]] south-west tile, which causes abnormally long hit delay when attacking a large NPC from the north or east. \n\n==Processing order delay==\nAttacks will hit on different ticks depending on whether the attacking or defending entity is processed first in a tick. If the entity receiving the hit is processed earlier than the entity dealing the hit, then the hit will be delayed by an additional one tick.\n\n[[NPCs]] are processed earlier than players each tick, so this effect will make all hits on [[NPCs]] delayed by an additional one tick compared to the numbers listed in this article.\n\nIn the case of [[PvP]], [[PID]] will be the determining factor whether or not processing order delay will delay attacks by one tick.\n\n==Melee==\nWhen attacking using a melee weapon, with few exceptions such as the [[Dragon_claws#Special_attack|dragon claws special attack]], the hit delay is 0 game ticks.\n\n==Ranged==\n=== Bows and crossbows ===\nBow and crossbow projectiles, with the exception of the [[dark bow]]'s second projectile, follow this table:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br/>(squares)\n!Hit delay<br/>(game ticks)\n|-\n|1\n|1\n|-\n|2\n|1\n|-\n|3\n|2\n|-\n|4\n|2\n|-\n|5\n|2\n|-\n|6\n|2\n|-\n|7\n|2\n|-\n|8\n|2\n|-\n|9\n|3\n|-\n|10\n|3\n|}\nThis delay follows this formula:\n\n:<math>\\mathit{BowDelay} = 1+\\left\\lfloor \\frac{3 + \\mathit{Distance}}{6} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n\n=== Dark bow ===\nThe [[dark bow]] has a unique hit delay defined for its second projectile, and its two projectiles follow this table:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br />\n!Hit delay<br />(1st projectile)\n!Hit delay\n(2nd projectile)\n|-\n|1\n|1\n|2\n|-\n|2\n|1\n|2\n|-\n|3\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|4\n|2\n|3\n|-\n|5\n|2\n|3\n|-\n|6\n|2\n|3\n|-\n|7\n|2\n|4\n|-\n|8\n|2\n|4\n|-\n|9\n|3\n|4\n|-\n|10\n|3\n|5\n|}\nThe first projectile follows the standard bow projectile delay formula:\n\n:<math>\\mathit{Bow Delay} = 1+ \\left\\lfloor \\frac{3 + \\mathit{Distance}}{6} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n\nThe second projectile follows a formula very similar to the magic formula:\n\n:<math>\\mathit{DarkBowDelay} = 1+ \\left\\lfloor \\frac{2 + \\mathit{Distance}}{3} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n\n=== Chinchompas and thrown category weapons ===\n[[Weapons/Types#Chinchompas|Chinchompas]] and [[Weapons/Types#Thrown weapons|thrown weapons]] ([[knives]], [[dart]]s, [[thrownaxes]], and the [[toxic blowpipe]]) have the following hit delay:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br />(squares)\n!Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n|-\n|1\n|1\n|-\n|2\n|1\n|-\n|3\n|1\n|-\n|4\n|1<ref name=blowp>The [[Toxic blowpipe#Special attack|toxic blowpipe special attack]] has a hit delay of 2 ticks when distance is 4 or 5.</ref>\n|-\n|5\n|1<ref name=blowp />\n|-\n|6\n|2\n|-\n|7\n|2\n|-\n|8\n|2\n|-\n|9\n|2\n|-\n|10\n|2\n|}\n{{Reflist}}\n\nThis delay follows the formula:\n\n:<math>\\mathit{ThrownDelay} = 1+ \\left\\lfloor \\frac{\\mathit{Distance}}{6} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n:\n\n=== Ballistae ===\n[[Ballista]]e have the following hit delay:\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br />(squares)\n!Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n|-\n|1\n|2\n|-\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|3\n|2\n|-\n|4\n|2\n|-\n|5\n|3\n|-\n|6\n|3\n|-\n|7\n|3\n|-\n|8\n|3\n|-\n|9\n|3\n|-\n|10\n|3\n|}\n=== Dwarf multicannon ===\nThe [[dwarf multicannon]], despite being able to attack targets at distances as far away as 19 tiles, does not have any hit delay.\n\n== Magic ==\nMost magic projectiles, including [[spells]] and projectiles from [[Weapons/Types#Powered staves|self-powered staves]], follow this table.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br />(squares)\n!Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n|-\n|1\n|1\n|-\n|2\n|2\n|-\n|3\n|2\n|-\n|4\n|2\n|-\n|5\n|3\n|-\n|6\n|3\n|-\n|7\n|3\n|-\n|8\n|4\n|-\n|9\n|4\n|-\n|10\n|4\n|-\n|11<ref name=barrage>[[Barrage spells]] calculate hit delay using the distance from an NPC's south-west tile, therefore hit delay can be observed for distances greater than 10 tiles on large [[NPCs]] such as [[Scorpia]].</ref>\n|5\n|-\n|12<ref name=barrage />\n|5\n|-\n|13<ref name=barrage />\n|5\n|-\n|14<ref name=barrage />\n|6\n|-\n|15<ref name=barrage />\n|6\n|}\n{{Reflist}}\nThis gives this likely formula:\n\n:<math>\\mathit{MagicDelay} = 1+ \\left\\lfloor \\frac{1 + \\mathit{Distance}}{3} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n\nHowever, [[grasp spells|grasp]] and [[demonbane spells]] from the [[Arceuus spellbook]] have a hit delay of 2 ticks no matter the distance between the caster and target.\n\n=== Shield specials ===\n\nShield special attacks such as the [[dragonfire shield]], [[dragonfire ward]], and [[ancient wyvern shield]] follow this table.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Distance<br />(squares)\n!Hit delay<br />(game ticks)\n|-\n|1\n|2\n|-\n|2\n|3\n|-\n|3\n|3\n|-\n|4\n|3\n|-\n|5\n|3\n|-\n|6\n|3\n|-\n|7\n|3\n|-\n|8\n|4\n|-\n|9\n|4\n|-\n|10\n|4\n|}\n\nThis gives the likely formula:\n:<math>2 + \\left\\lfloor \\frac{4+\\mathit{Distance}}{6} \\right\\rfloor</math>\n\n[[Category:Mechanics]]\n{{Combat Mechanics}}"}